node.text:
"We don’t have to choose between using energy and protecting the planet."

@unep Young Champion of the Earth Nzambi Matee explains the role sustainable energy plays in building a better future for all. 
 
"Imagine a world where every job is based on clean, renewable energy – and where wind and solar are even more abundant. And where energy is affordable and reliable – and available to everyone. This might sound like a fantasy – but it’s achievable and we know how to get there."

The #ParisAgreement on the climate emergency is our roadmap for moving to a low-carbon economy and achieving a sustainable future. Since this international #ClimateAction treaty opened for signature 5 years ago, almost 200 countries have signed on to tackle the climate crisis together to limit global warming to protect people and planet.

 #GlobalGoals #ActNow

"My warmest wishes to everyone celebrating #EidAlFitr," #UnitedNations Secretary-General @antonioguterres said on Wednesday.

"I was delighted to mark the end of Ramadan with Asia El-Sayeed Ali, a Yemeni health worker helping malnourished children and mothers in a @worldfoodprogramme-supported nutrition clinic.

Asia personifies core values of Ramadan: compassion and empathy. Her resilience in the face of the devastating conflict in Yemen, as well as her life-saving work in support of people in desperate need have moved me greatly.

As #Ramadan comes to an end, let us continue drawing inspiration from its many lessons of solidarity that are celebrated during this Holy Month."

Regram: @antonioguterres

#ActNow #GlobalGoals

@unep Goodwill Ambassador @aidanrgallagher describes how the #ParisAgreement can help us create a world free from the threats of the climate crisis. 

"This is personal for me," he explains. "I don’t want to choke on the air I breathe, or see wildfires burning out of control. So let’s keep working together. And you too can protect what is left and repair what has been damaged."

On Thursday's #EarthDay, @antonioguterres will be joining the U.S. Leaders’ Summit on Climate to reiterate his call for urgent #ClimateAction. 

"The Paris Agreement is our pact with our children, grandchildren & the whole human family," said the Secretary-General. 

"The climate crisis is the race of our lifetimes. We must go much further, and much faster."

#GenerationRestoration #ForNature

All children have the right to a happy and healthy childhood, free from discrimination and full of love and acceptance. And acceptance begins at home. Every child should grow up in safe, loving and nurturing environment.

No child should suffer because of who they are. All children deserve protection and equal rights. Let's see kids the way they see themselves.

On Wednesday's International Transgender Day of Visibility, join @unaidsglobal in calling for the rights of transgender children to be protected.

#TransDayOfVisibility #SeeMeAsIAm

node.text:
Checkmate! ⁣♚♕

A young child from South Sudan plays chess in a mental health centre in Ethiopia.

Tuesday's #WorldChessDay is an opportunity to celebrate the ways in which chess can foster dialogue, solidarity and a culture of peace.⁣

Throughout history, games and sports have helped humanity to survive times of crisis by reducing anxieties and improving mental health. While #COVID19 has forced many sports activities to scale down, chess has demonstrated remarkable resilience and adaptability during the pandemic.

Regram: @refugees 📸: UNHCR / Linda Muriuki⁣

Eid Mubarak!

As people around the world celebrate #EidAlAdha, each of us can draw encouragement from the values of solidarity, empathy and compassion that are inspired by Eid.

node.text:
Farmer Immaculée shares a smile while she spends some time in one of her fields in #Rwanda.

The local farmer cultivates fresh crops that help feed her community. "It feels good to know that your produce is reaching children in your very own community," explains Immaculée, who is part of a farmers' cooperative that receives support from the World Food Programme (WFP).

Thanks to adequate training and WFP’s Farm to Market Alliance programme, Immaculée is able to sell her crops through the farmers' cooperative.

WFP is working to empower smallholder farmers in Rwanda through agricultural training and greater access to national and regional markets, while also delivering school meals to children across the country.

Regram: @worldfoodprogramme I 📷: WFP / Arete / Fredrik Lerneryd

#GlobalGoals #ZerHunger

node.text:
A large flock of flamingos takes flight in #Kazakhstan.

The country, which lies on the migration route of flamingos and dozens of other birds, offers suitable nesting grounds. During the nesting period, the shores of the country's Kurgaldzhinsky Reserve fill with up to 70,000 birds.

Habitat loss and poaching are posing a risk to to flamingos and other birds, a situation which is further exacerbated by the climate crisis.

The #UnitedNations Development Programme (UNDP) is working to protect biodiversity and counter habitat loss, while stressing the importance of taking #ClimateAction.

Regram: @undpeurasia I 📸: Victoria Kovshar / UNDP Kazakhstan

#GlobalGoals

node.text:
Children gather around their tents in a displacement settlement in Afghanistan.

They are among the almost 5 million people who have been internally displaced across the country. Ongoing conflict and the resulting displacement continue to exacerbate the humanitarian crisis in Afghanistan, where an additional 200,000 people were forced to flee their homes in 2021.

This year, nearly half of the population will need humanitarian assistance. The #UnitedNations office for humanitarian affairs (OCHA) is working with its partners to provide emergency assistance to those most in need, including food, water, medicine and more.

Regram: @un_ocha I 📷: UNOCHA / Fariba Housaini

#GlobalGoals

node.text:
Empowering children to be heroic and impactful leaders for change is crucial for our shared future. Our #ClimateAction Superheroes can help engage and educate children on how to #ActNow to address the climate emergency.

Meet just a few of our Superheroes: 
💡 The Energy Expert never wastes electricity.
👖 The Fashion Fixer promotes zero-waste fashion. 
🌊 The Waste Wizard keeps dangerous plastics out of the ocean. 
🗣 The Truth Talker shares scientific facts about the climate crisis. 

You and the children in your life can join these superheroes in protecting our planet and contributing to a better future for all.

node.text:
Nelson Mandela addresses the Special Committee Against Apartheid in the #UnitedNations General Assembly Hall in June 1990.

"We hold it as an inviolable principle that racism must be opposed by all the means that humanity has at its disposal. Wherever it occurs it has the potential to result in a systematic and comprehensive denial of human rights to those who are discriminated against," he said. 

Nelson Mandela’s journey from prisoner to President of South Africa was the triumph of an extraordinary individual against the forces of hate, ignorance and fear – and it was a testimony to the power of courage, reconciliation and forgiveness to overcome the injustice of racial discrimination. 

Sunday's #MandelaDay is an opportunity to learn from Nelson Mandela's example to #StandUp4HumanRights and #FightRacism. "Let us be inspired by Madiba’s message that each of us can make a difference in promoting peace, human rights, harmony with nature and dignity for all," said #UnitedNations Secretary-General @antonioguterres.

📷: UN Photo / P. Sudhakaran 

#NelsonMandela #UNGA #GlobalGoals

node.text:
25-year-old farmer Mamie from Sierra Leone smiles happily as she carries her little one on her back.

Despite being a fertile country, only 2% of farmers in Sierra Leone produce enough crops to meet their family's food needs for a whole year. As a result, many young people are moving away from agriculture as a way of life. 

The World Food Programme (WFP) is working to help modernize agriculture by providing knowledge and tools to increase productivity, while creating profitable youth employment opportunities.

Regram: @worldfoodprogramme I 📷: WFP / Evelyn Fey

#ZeroHunger

The #UnitedNations works for everyone, everywhere — by tackling #COVID19, preventing conflict, vaccinating children, protecting refugees, feeding the hungry, addressing the climate emergency, empowering women, responding to humanitarian crises, and so much more.

node.text:
Mother Naina Patel and her daughter Mamta Diwas share a smile during a routine immunization and medical check-up at a health clinic in #India.

Despite global vaccination rates rising from 20% to 83% in the 1980s, the world has seen an alarming drop in vaccination rates during the pandemic.

Disruptions in health services due to #COVID19 resulted in 23 million children missing out on vaccines in 2020 – 3.7 million more than in 2019. 

@unicef and the World Health Organization (@who) are stressing the urgent need to invest in childhood vaccination efforts to ensure every child is able to receive life-saving vaccines.

Regram: @unicef I 📸: © UNICEF/UNI341190/Panjwani

#VaccinesWork #ForEveryChild #GlobalGoals

node.text:
Regram: @antonioguterres

In a few days, athletes from around the world will come together for the #Tokyo2020 Olympic and Paralympic Games. They have had to overcome enormous obstacles to participate, amid the #COVID19 pandemic.

We need to show the same strength and solidarity in our efforts to bring peace to our world.

Today, I have called for all parties to conflict to observe this silencing of the guns, while the Olympic and Paralympic Games proceed. People and nations can build on this Olympic Truce to establish lasting ceasefires and find paths towards sustainable peace.

Seeking peace and uniting around common goals is even more important this year, as we strive to end the pandemic and build a strong, sustainable and inclusive global recovery.

Regram: @antonioguterres | 📷: UN Photo / Michos Tzovaras

#Olympics #Paralympics #GlobalGoals

node.text:
Young women in #Bangladesh participate in a training session on computer programming. 

Young people have been particularly exposed to the socio-economic consequences of the pandemic, including learning and training losses due to lockdowns. 

More than ever, it is crucial to ensure the continuity of skills development and to reinforce high quality education and training programmes to equip youth with the competencies they need for the future.

On Thursday’s World Youth Skills Day, join us in celebrating the importance of youth skills development and recognizing the key role of young people in building a more sustainable future. 

Regram: @unesco I 📸: © UNESCO-UNEVOC/Momin Abdul

#WorldYouthSkillsDay #GlobalGoals
